## Key Engineering Decisions & Non-obvious Parts

### 1. Slot Conflict Detection
```python
# In appointment_service.py вЂ” use SELECT FOR UPDATE to prevent race conditions
async def book_appointment(db, patient_id, doctor_id, slot_id, date):
    async with db.begin():
        existing = await db.execute(
            select(Appointment)
            .where(Appointment.doctor_id == doctor_id)
            .where(Appointment.date == date)
            .where(Appointment.slot_id == slot_id)
            .where(Appointment.status.notin_(["cancelled", "no_show"]))
            .with_for_update()  # DB-level lock
        )
        if existing.scalar():
            raise ConflictError("Slot already booked")
        # create appointment ...
```

### 2. Queue Position Calculation
```python
# Not just "position 4 of 10" вЂ” accounts for cancellations and in-progress
def calculate_queue_position(appointments: list, patient_id: int) -> dict:
    active = [a for a in appointments if a.status not in ("cancelled", "no_show", "done")]
    position = next((i+1 for i, a in enumerate(active) if a.patient_id == patient_id), None)
    ahead = position - 1 if position else 0
    eta_minutes = ahead * AVG_CONSULT_MINUTES
    return {"position": position, "ahead": ahead, "eta_minutes": eta_minutes}
```

### 3. Single-Use Refresh Tokens (Token Rotation)
```python
# Redis key: refresh:<token_hash> в†’ user_id, TTL 7 days
# On refresh: DELETE old key, issue new token pair
# On logout: DELETE key immediately в†’ invalidated even if stolen
```

### 4. Audit Log Immutability
```python
# No update/delete methods exist on AuditLog model
# All inserts happen via middleware вЂ” not manually in service layer
# This ensures no service can skip audit logging
```

